  "body": "Hello,\n\nI have a breaking change upgrading from 0.12 to 0.13. \n\nI have a component that uses inline styles, and in one state it uses inline styles and in the other it does not need them so i set style to null. In react 12 this worked fine, but now it fails to update the inline styles.\n\nHere is an example of a component that isolates the issue:\n\n``` jsx\nReact.createClass({\n  getInitialState: function () {\n    return {\n      isRed: false\n    };\n  },\n\n  toggleRed: function () {\n    this.setState({\n      isRed: !this.state.isRed\n    });\n  },\n\n  componentDidMount: function () {\n    setInterval(this.toggleRed, 700);\n  },\n\n  render: function () {\n\n    var style = null; // This does not work\n    // var style = {}; // THIS WORKS\n\n    if (this.state.isRed) {\n      style = {\n        color: 'red'\n      };\n    }\n\n    return (\n      <div style={style}>\n        {this.state.isRed ? 'Is Red' : 'Is Black'}\n      </div>\n    );\n  }\n});\n```\n",
